               <p>THOMAS WINMILL. I am a <rs id="t18300415-305-viclabel1658" type="occupation">grocer</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300415-305-victim2552 t18300415-305-viclabel1658"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18300415-305-crimeloc1659">Carnaby-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18300415-305-crimeloc1659" type="placeName" value="Carnaby-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18300415-305-crimeloc1659" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300415-305-off1656 t18300415-305-crimeloc1659"></join>. I was out at the time this happened.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300415-305-person2553">
                  JOHN 
                  MATTHEWS
               <interp inst="t18300415-305-person2553" type="surname" value="MATTHEWS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-305-person2553" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-305-person2553" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live in Marlborough-court, near the prosecutor's; I saw the prisoner near his shop, with three other persons - the prisoner went and asked for one halfpenny worth of Spanish liquorice, while one of the others took the soap from the counter; the prisoner then took the soap - I gave an alarm, and he was taken in Maddox-street, with the soap, which he dropped.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300415-305-person2554">
                  WILLIAM 
                  DODD
               <interp inst="t18300415-305-person2554" type="surname" value="DODD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-305-person2554" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-305-person2554" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I saw the prisoner put the soap under his coat, as I was standing in Lowndes-court; we went and asked at the prosecutor's shop, if they had lost any thing - they said Yes, a piece of soap; we pursued the prisoner and met an officer, who took him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300415-305-person2555">
                  JOHN 
                  ANDERSON
               <interp inst="t18300415-305-person2555" type="surname" value="ANDERSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-305-person2555" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-305-person2555" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I took the prisoner - this is the soap.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was standing still when they took me; the soap was on before me. I went to buy the Spanish liquorice, and one of the boys took the soap; I did not. GUILTY.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300415-305-person2556">
                  EDWARD 
                  BURRIDGE
               <interp inst="t18300415-305-person2556" type="surname" value="BURRIDGE"></interp>
